In this proclamation issued by President Donald J. Trump on November 7, 2017, he honors and pays respect to the veterans of the United States. He acknowledges their bravery and service in the military, and emphasizes the importance of caring for veterans after they return to civilian life. The president mentions his administration's commitment to providing the best support and resources to service members and improving veterans' healthcare. He also highlights his signing of legislation to improve accountability at the Department of Veterans Affairs and to give veterans lifetime GI Bill education benefits. Additionally, President Trump mentions his upcoming visit to Vietnam on Veterans Day, where he will recognize the sacrifices of the Vietnam veterans and work towards accounting for the missing soldiers. The proclamation concludes by designating November 11, 2017, as Veterans Day and encouraging all Americans to honor veterans through public ceremonies and private thoughts and prayers.